}, {"kind": "text", "text": "), or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a long cough, and attended with constant fever."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence the saying, in a trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gubaAru*ayoli AlmaroA^api", "text_ar": "غُبَارُذَيْلِ المَرْاَةِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlfaAjirapi yuwrvu Als~il~a", "text_ar": "الفَاجِرَةِ يُورثُ السِّلَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The dust of the skirt of the vitious woman occasions the loss of property"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; meaning that he who follows vitious women and acts vitiously, loses his property, and becomes poor: the diminution and departure of property being likened to the diminution and wasting away of the body when one has the disorder termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sil~", "text_ar": "سِلّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "M", "Msb", "K", "TA", "T"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}